SeriesTypeDescriptions.Arearange: Arearange charts are line charts displaying a range between a lower and higher value for each point.
SeriesTypeDescriptions.Areasplinerange: These charts are line charts displaying a range between a lower and higher value for each point.
SeriesTypeDescriptions.Boxplot: Box plot charts are typically used to display groups of statistical data. Each data point in the chart can have up to 5 values: minimum, lower quartile, median, upper quartile, and maximum.
SeriesTypeDescriptions.Bubble: Bubble charts are scatter charts where each data point also has a size value.
SeriesTypeDescriptions.Columnrange: Columnrange charts are column charts displaying a range between a lower and higher value for each point.
SeriesTypeDescriptions.Errorbar: Errorbar series are used to display the variability of the data.
SeriesTypeDescriptions.Funnel: Funnel charts are used to display reduction of data in stages.
SeriesTypeDescriptions.Pyramid: Pyramid charts consist of a single pyramid with item heights corresponding to each point value.
SeriesTypeDescriptions.Waterfall: A waterfall chart is a column chart where each column contributes towards a total end value.
